[I] Low-level user-space library for the DRM/KMS subsystem

[T] Libdrm provides a thin user-space interface to the Linux DRM/KMS subsystem,
[T] enabling modesetting, buffer management, and low-level GPU access for
[T] drivers and graphics stacks like Mesa, Wayland, and Xorg. It comes with
[T] small test and demo programs, like modeprint and modetesti, for exercising
[T] DRM and KMS functionality.

